/polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption"> Photo by <a href="https://unsplash.com/@jaison333?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Jaison Lin</a> on <a href="https://unsplash.com/photos/crowd-surrounded-by-trees-during-daytime-Z1Q44ZgVMQ0?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Unsplash</a></figcaption></figure></div><p> These are called zakkyo buildings. The word roughly translates to “miscellaneous”. They contain a whole bunch of small retail businesses — restaurants, bars, retail outlets, schools, health care offices, whatever. Sometimes there are dozens of these in a single building. None of the businesses are related to each other; you just rent out a space in a zakkyo.</p><p> The distinctive look of a zakkyo building — and from whole streets of zakkyo buildings packed together — comes from Japanese architectural codes. Building tall-ish, narrow buildings was a way to maximize usable floor space within the rules of the postwar period. Japanese laws also allow for a lot of different types of businesses to coexist in any given space — there are basically no regulations on serving alcohol. Some buildings also have external elevators and/or staircases, which makes it easy to get up to a top-floor store from the street.</p><p> But perhaps most importantly, Japanese regulations were and are very lenient about allowing a bunch of electric signs, including signs that hang out into the street. Even as Simon and Garfunkel were decrying the “ <a href="https://genius.com/Simon-and-garfunkel-the-sound-of-silence-lyrics">neon god</a> ” of urban modernity, Japan was embracing a libertarian approach to small business. Putting a restaurant on the 4th floor of a building often only makes sense if you can inform passing pedestrians that there&#39;s a restaurant up there — which means having a big glowing sign.</p><p> Add these all up, and it made economic sense to cram a whole bunch of small businesses into the upper floors of buildings in the city center. So Japan did. And in doing so, it created one of the world&#39;s most distinctive and beautiful modern urban landscapes, even as other cities&#39; old-fashioned aesthetic preferences caused them to restrict electric signage. Now people come from all over the world to take pictures of Tokyo&#39;s beautiful streetscapes.</p><p> But zakkyo buildings have a benefit that goes way beyond aesthetics. When you can stack a bunch of retail businesses vertically, you can cram a whole lot of retail into a very small part of a city.这些零售中心——比如涩谷市中心、新宿等——变得非常拥挤。 </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F421cd409-c230-43a6-a298-d2cab8b81dc1_951x634.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F421cd409-c230-43a6-a298-d2cab8b81dc1_951x634.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F421cd409-c230-43a6-a298-d2cab8b81dc1_951x634.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F421cd409-c230-43a6-a298-d2cab8b81dc1_951x634.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F421cd409-c230-43a6-a298-d2cab8b81dc1_951x634.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F421cd409-c230-43a6-a298-d2cab8b81dc1_951x634.jpeg" width="951" height="634" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/421cd409-c230-43a6-a298-d2cab8b81dc1_951x634.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:634,&quot;width&quot;:951,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:346913,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F421cd409-c230-43a6-a298-d2cab8b81dc1_951x634.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F421cd409-c230-43a6-a298-d2cab8b81dc1_951x634.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F421cd409-c230-43a6-a298-d2cab8b81dc1_951x634.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F421cd409-c230-43a6-a298-d2cab8b81dc1_951x634.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">照片由<a href="https://unsplash.com/@jezar?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Jezael Melgoza</a>在<a href="https://unsplash.com/photos/people-gathered-outside-buildings-and-vehicles-alY6_OpdwRQ?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Unsplash</a>上拍摄</figcaption></figure></div><p>但这使得城市的更多住宅区绿树成荫且安静，即使它们仅相隔几个街区！从上面的路口步行只需几分钟，就到达一条安静的后街，两旁都是房屋。</p><p>在人口稠密的城市，零售业主要局限于建筑物的一楼，零售业必须更加分散于整个城市。这意味着，如果您要去购物，您必须步行或乘坐长途火车才能看到一大堆不同的商店。这也意味着很多人的公寓位于喧闹的零售店和拥挤的街道上方。</p><p>换句话说，纽约市和其他人口稠密的城市可以使用一些扎京建筑。允许外部电子标志和方便的街道通向顶层，并且允许零售垂直集中，而不必遍布整个城市。你可以从购物者难以置信的多样性中受益，同时你可以让很多人的公寓楼免受脚步声、喊叫声、送货卡车和关上车门的声音的影响。</p><p>而且，它看起来非常酷。</p><h4>袖珍社区</h4><p>许多古老的日本建筑都是由木头制成的，即使它们的外立面看起来像石头或混凝土。这是一个巨大的火灾隐患，尤其是在像东京这样建筑物密集的城市。因此，为了遏制可能的火灾蔓延，东京建造了一系列大型街道，前面是巨型混凝土建筑，作为天然防火带。</p><p>这对城市景观产生了非常有趣的影响。它创造了阿尔马桑和他的合著者所说的“袖珍”社区，其中密集的小街道和低层建筑迷宫般，被基本上是巨大的墙壁所遮挡。这是一个真实社区的图表： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55f7329e-ff62-431f-bee5-7355d2a15625_726x723.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55f7329e-ff62-431f-bee5-7355d2a15625_726x723.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55f7329e-ff62-431f-bee5-7355d2a15625_726x723.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55f7329e-ff62-431f-bee5-7355d2a15625_726x723.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55f7329e-ff62-431f-bee5-7355d2a15625_726x723.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55f7329e-ff62-431f-bee5-7355d2a15625_726x723.jpeg" width="654" height="651.297520661157" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/55f7329e-ff62-431f-bee5-7355d2a15625_726x723.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:723,&quot;width&quot;:726,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:654,&quot;bytes&quot;:278899,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55f7329e-ff62-431f-bee5-7355d2a15625_726x723.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55f7329e-ff62-431f-bee5-7355d2a15625_726x723.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55f7329e-ff62-431f-bee5-7355d2a15625_726x723.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55f7329e-ff62-431f-bee5-7355d2a15625_726x723.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption"> Source: <em>Emergent Tokyo</em> via <a href="https://www.mercatus.org/research/working-papers/understanding-tokyos-land-use-power-microspaces">McReynolds (2022)</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>这意味着，如果你在口袋里，你就不会遇到很多汽车。汽车仍然可以进入里面，进入迷宫般的小街道，但它们通常不会这样做，因为沿着口袋外的大街道几乎总是更容易。因此，袖珍社区变得非常安静祥和，你可以到处走动，不用担心被车撞，也不必吸入汽车尾气。 It cuts down on noise, too.</p><p>这些袖珍社区实现了“<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/City_block#Superblock">超级街区</a>”应该实现的目标，但很少做到。大多数现实世界的“超级街区”要么非常小——比如<a href="https://www.citiesforum.org/news/superblock-superilla-barcelona-a-city-redefined/">巴塞罗那的“超级街区”</a> ，虽然很可爱，但实际上只是单个街区——要么就是<a href="https://images.seattletimes.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/05252023_China-Vacant-Buildings_1154342.jpg?d=780x438">像中国那样</a>贫瘠的“公园塔”怪物。东京在很大程度上是偶然实现了世界各地的超级街区规划者未能通过设计实现的目标。</p><p>这些袖珍社区还体现了日本城市化的一个更普遍的特征——缺乏任何形式的网格规划。在谷歌地图发明之前，这使得开车在日本城市中导航变得很痛苦。但这也意味着小巷明确是行人优先，而不是汽车优先。如果您开车，请尽量走大路，否则您很容易在蜿蜒的小巷迷宫中迷路。这样行人就可以自由行走。</p><p>相比之下，在纽约市，网格规划意味着汽车可以轻松地使用小型住宅街道在一条大路和另一条大路之间行驶。他们就是这么做的。这意味着，无论您在曼哈顿或行政区内部的街道有多小，您都无法真正走在街道中间。这意味着每条街道都必须有人行道，这限制了密度并减少了人们在社区行走的公共空间。这是一种完全不同的城市体验。它让您在世界上发达国家最密集的城市景观之一中获得低交通郊区社区的感觉。</p><p>当然，许多大城市的街道规划现已到位——纽约永远不会改用蜿蜒的小巷，因为这需要大规模的重建。但是，如果您正在达拉斯、休斯顿、菲尼克斯或任何其他地方建设新的市中心区域，您可能需要考虑为大街道制定网格规划，但为人们建造蜿蜒、环形的小街道供人们行走。</p><h4>自下而上的组织</h4><p>正如我在<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/why-japanese-cities-are-such-nice">上一篇文章</a>中所写，日本最大的城市规划优势之一是混合用途社区。即使是郊区的住宅区，周围也会散布一些企业——自行车店、咖啡馆、社区酒吧、小布料店等等。在美国，如果你想离开家去喝杯咖啡、啤酒或吃点东西，你通常必须跳上你的车，开车到某个地方，然后停在那里——或者至少使用自行车。在日本，您可能仍然骑自行车或乘坐火车，但如果您愿意，您可以<em>步行</em>到附近的咖啡馆、酒吧或面店。混合用途分区创造了步行便利性。</p><p>许多美国人一想到他们郊区的房子旁边有一家酒吧、一家餐馆，甚至一家商店，就会惊恐万状。其实很多日本人都会有同感！但在日本，社区可以通过多种方式与当地企业合作，确保保留社区的特色。麦克雷诺兹写道：</p><blockquote><p>在东京，隔壁的破坏性酒吧也不受欢迎。然而，存在一定程度的法律模糊性，这促使邻国就国内企业进行谈判达成相互可以接受的共识。 Under Tokyo&#39;s zoning regulations…dual-use residences are permitted by right;然而，法规还禁止在此过程中对邻居造成不合理的滋扰。当地的邻里协会（自治会或自治会，字面意思是“自治协会”）经常会调解邻居之间关于不合理或不合理的纠纷；如果不能达成共识，那么实际上最终的裁决者将是东京都警察局的当地分支机构……考虑到在纠纷中传唤警察所带来的风险和不确定性，大多数邻居更愿意在争议中达成共识只要有可能，他们自己。</p></blockquote><p>通过陈旧、过时的刻板印象来解读日本的人们可能会认为这是集体主义的标志。事实上，这些邻里协会是自下而上的自组织的标志，也是一种将政府当局拒之门外的愿望——这是日本令人惊讶的自由主义、自下而上文化的标志。</p><p>我看到这种自下而上的社区组织在美国有很大的潜力<a href="https://worksinprogress.co/issue/houston-we-have-a-solution/">安雅·马丁（Anya Martin）最近发表的一篇文章</a>记录了休斯顿如何能够在住宅区建造大量“缺失的中间”住房——本质上是通过为每个微型社区提供支持控制是否允许密度。如果美国城市采用日本式的混合用途分区，他们可以使用类似的“社区控制”机制，允许社区允许餐馆、商店甚至酒吧，并选择允许<em>哪些</em>。</p><p>同样， <em>《Emergent Tokyo》</em>记录了日本许多独特的商业空间——横丁小巷、地下购物商场、商店街、甚至一些座桥建筑——受到抵制重建压力的小型商业协会的保护。例如，每个去东京的游客都喜欢去黄金街喝一杯，这是新宿后面迷宫般的小酒吧区： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0a57bb5e-acd3-412c-95bb-b32588fb7e67_1024x768.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0a57bb5e-acd3-412c-95bb-b32588fb7e67_1024x768.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0a57bb5e-acd3-412c-95bb-b32588fb7e67_1024x768.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0a57bb5e-acd3-412c-95bb-b32588fb7e67_1024x768.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0a57bb5e-acd3-412c-95bb-b32588fb7e67_1024x768.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0a57bb5e-acd3-412c-95bb-b32588fb7e67_1024x768.jpeg" width="1024" height="768" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/0a57bb5e-acd3-412c-95bb-b32588fb7e67_1024x768.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:768,&quot;width&quot;:1024,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:398156,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0a57bb5e-acd3-412c-95bb-b32588fb7e67_1024x768.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0a57bb5e-acd3-412c-95bb-b32588fb7e67_1024x768.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0a57bb5e-acd3-412c-95bb-b32588fb7e67_1024x768.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0a57bb5e-acd3-412c-95bb-b32588fb7e67_1024x768.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption"> “<a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/95572727@N00/47846539792">更多东京黄金街</a>”作者： <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/95572727@N00">Trey Ratcliff</a> ， <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.0/?ref=openverse">CC BY-NC-SA 2.0</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>好吧，金街之所以仍然存在，而不是很久以前就被推平成购物中心，是因为该地区所有的小商人在 20 世纪 80 年代<a href="http://golden-gai.tokyo/en/history/">联合起来抵制重建压力</a>。</p><p>这一事件以及许多其他类似的事件证明了<em>商业邻避主义</em>在创造独特且有趣的城市体验方面的有用性。我花了很多时间谴责<em>住宅邻避主义</em>阻碍新住房建设。住宅邻避主义很糟糕！但小企业阻碍大企业虽然在经济上效率不高，但却可以产生积极的溢出效应——它让城市保持其独特的特征，而不是全部变成一个全球化标准城市的千篇一律的版本。小企业的邻避主义最终是游客涌向日本的原因之一。</p><p>这让我想到了<em>新兴东京</em>遗漏的最重要的事情——小企业保护对日本城市化和日本社会的核心作用。</p><h4>日本的秘诀是小企业</h4><p>大东京地区<a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2008/02/24/business/worldbusiness/24guide.html">有 160,000 家餐厅</a>。纽约都会区有 25,000 人。巴黎大都市区只有13,000人。东京人口较多，但即使考虑到这一点，它的餐饮场所种类也远远超过纽约市的两倍。其中大多数是小型企业，而不是大型连锁企业。事实证明，这不仅对日本优秀的城市化至关重要，而且对日本的中产阶级也至关重要。</p><p> <em>Emergent Tokyo</em>的大部分内容致力于讨论日本独特的商业空间——横丁、地下拱廊等。这里还有几张照片： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5d2565ef-cd87-441e-a4bb-91dab2ea2067_416x624.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5d2565ef-cd87-441e-a4bb-91dab2ea2067_416x624.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5d2565ef-cd87-441e-a4bb-91dab2ea2067_416x624.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5d2565ef-cd87-441e-a4bb-91dab2ea2067_416x624.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5d2565ef-cd87-441e-a4bb-91dab2ea2067_416x624.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5d2565ef-cd87-441e-a4bb-91dab2ea2067_416x624.jpeg" width="416" height="624" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/5d2565ef-cd87-441e-a4bb-91dab2ea2067_416x624.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:624,&quot;width&quot;:416,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:126896,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5d2565ef-cd87-441e-a4bb-91dab2ea2067_416