p,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9981d368-b4a9-4d1a-accc-fcdede71f9d4_530x795.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9981d368-b4a9-4d1a-accc-fcdede71f9d4_530x795.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9981d368-b4a9-4d1a-accc-fcdede71f9d4_530x795.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9981d368-b4a9-4d1a-accc-fcdede71f9d4_530x795.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9981d368-b4a9-4d1a-accc-fcdede71f9d4_530x795.jpeg" width="530" height="795" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/9981d368-b4a9-4d1a-accc-fcdede71f9d4_530x795.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:795,&quot;width&quot;:530,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:193185,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9981d368-b4a9-4d1a-accc-fcdede71f9d4_530x795.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9981d368-b4a9-4d1a-accc-fcdede71f9d4_530x795.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9981d368-b4a9-4d1a-accc-fcdede71f9d4_530x795.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9981d368-b4a9-4d1a-accc-fcdede71f9d4_530x795.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption"> <a href="https://unsplash.com/@chrisyangchrisfilm?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">克里斯·杨 (Chris Yang)</a>在<a href="https://unsplash.com/photos/man-walking-between-stores-during-night-time-LA57RXF1mSI?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Unsplash</a>上拍摄的照片</figcaption></figure></div><p>对于这些案例中的每一个，故事都是一样的。该空间之所以蓬勃发展，是因为<em>商业密度</em>高——在一个小区域内挤满了各种各样的企业。正如我在<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/why-japanese-cities-are-such-nice">上一篇文章</a>中所写，商业密度的讨论严重不足。它允许<em>多样化</em>——在日本，当你出去吃饭时，有上百万家餐馆可供选择，而且它们都彼此靠近。当你去买衣服时，有一百万家小精品店可供尝试，而且它们都彼此靠近。这极大地增强了购物体验。</p><p>但这不仅仅是多样性；它的<em>独特性</em>。如果你走进一座杂协大楼，里面只有橄榄园、星巴克或 24 小时健身中心，过一段时间就会变得很无聊。日本都市的浪漫之处在于，总有许多全新的地方值得探索，因此四处走走并发现新事物总是值得的。</p><p>除非有大量的人想要创办小企业，否则这种情况不可能发生。 <em>Emergent Tokyo</em>所谈论的每一个商业空间——横町、扎京、地下拱廊——都取决于一群想要在那里落户的小企业。如果没有这种需求，这些空间要么空置，要么被链条填满。如果没有小型企业协会联合起来抵抗重建压力，日本最具标志性的城市空间最终将变成无聊的企业购物中心——不是因为资本主义无形的罪恶，而仅仅是因为没有小型企业，就没有什么可做的。那个空间<em>除了</em>在那里放一个无聊的企业购物中心之外。</p><p> <em>《新兴东京》</em>从未深入探讨日本<em>为何</em>如此以小企业为中心。部分原因是政策驱动——日本制定了多项政府政策来支持小型零售企业而不是大型零售企业。其中之一是《 <a href="https://spinup-000d1a-wp-offload-media.s3.amazonaws.com/faculty/wp-content/uploads/sites/53/2019/06/WhySmallShops.Mak.SS.1998.pdf">大型商店法》</a> ，该法不鼓励在人口稠密的城市地区开设大型商店。但还有很多其他的。有大量专门针对小型零售企业的补贴和支持——启动成本援助、装修援助、低息贷款、税收优惠、小企业企业家培训、社区保护法等等。当美国人发现在日本开设小型零售企业是多么容易时，他们常常会感到惊讶： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F884586be-a633-418a-a535-826c54f84c36_907x777.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F884586be-a633-418a-a535-826c54f84c36_907x777.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F884586be-a633-418a-a535-826c54f84c36_907x777.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F884586be-a633-418a-a535-826c54f84c36_907x777.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F884586be-a633-418a-a535-826c54f84c36_907x777.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F884586be-a633-418a-a535-826c54f84c36_907x777.jpeg" width="606" height="519.1422271223814" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/884586be-a633-418a-a535-826c54f84c36_907x777.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:777,&quot;width&quot;:907,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:606,&quot;bytes&quot;:193946,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F884586be-a633-418a-a535-826c54f84c36_907x777.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F884586be-a633-418a-a535-826c54f84c36_907x777.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F884586be-a633-418a-a535-826c54f84c36_907x777.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F884586be-a633-418a-a535-826c54f84c36_907x777.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>在我看来，除了使城市环境变得愉快和令人兴奋之外，小企业主还为日本城市主义的许多基本要素提供了重要的支持者。</p><p>以公共安全为例。当一家连锁店<a href="https://www.foxbusiness.com/retail/cvs-store-close-dc-thieves-ransack-location-months-leaving-shelves-bare">被抢劫</a>时，该公司并没有倒闭，而是倒闭了。其庞大的商店网络可以吸收损失。但当一家小型独立商店遭到抢劫时，店主的损失往往是毁灭性的。因此，小企业主对促进公共安全的政策很感兴趣，而公共安全是日本优秀城市的关键要素之一。</p><p>另一个例子是步行性。连锁店具有知名度和营销预算；城市地区的小型独立餐馆和商店更多地依赖于偶然的人流量。因此，拥有良好的火车、适宜步行的空间和住宅密度符合小商人的利益，以便为他们带来更多的客户。当人们问为什么日本拥有世界上最好的火车系统时，很少提及小企业的政治力量，但这似乎是一个值得探讨的因素。</p><p>小企业为资本主义本身创造了最终的支持者。中央计划经济体很少有<em>《新兴东京》</em>中所描述的那种自发的、充满活力的商业空间。小企业将大量中产阶级转变为资本家，让他们直接参与私营企业所有制。他们强烈倾向于<a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/on-small-business/wp/2016/10/12/study-republicans-are-24-percent-more-likely-than-democrats-to-be-business-owners/">投票给支持商业的政党</a>。</p><p>在美国，小型“夫妻店”零售企业自 20 世纪中叶以来<a href="https://www.nber.org/books-and-chapters/producer-dynamics-new-evidence-micro-data/role-retail-chains-national-regional-and-industry-results">一直在消失</a>，因为大型连锁店利用其<a href="https://www2.census.gov/ces/wp/2015/CES-WP-15-10.pdf">较高的生产率</a>将其挤出市场。日本顽强地抵制了这一趋势，而正是这一点使得日本的城市比美国的城市更加充满活力并维持更多的商业多样性。效率是有代价的，但便宜的东西并不是这个世界上唯一令人愉快的事情。</p><p>如果美国大城市愿意的话，他们可以改变这一现状。 <a href="https://www.retaildive.com/news/banning-sameness-how-retailers-can-work-with-cities-chain-store-restric/388183/">已经有一项限制市中心连锁店的运动</a>，但需要与鼓励、培训和支持小型独立零售企业的措施相结合。分区改革必须成为其中的一部分，并且应放松对酒类许可证和电子标志的许可要求和限制等规定。当然，如果要实现这一目标，步行便利性、交通和公共安全都需要得到改善。 If cities can bring themselves to do all these things, I think they can create, if not a replica of the Japanese urban experience, then at least something a lot more in that direction than what exists now.</p><p> In fact, small businesses are now <a href="https://www.economist.com/asia/2021/12/04/japans-small-businesses-are-in-trouble">under threat in Japan</a> , due to a lack of young people who want to take over family businesses. This is a big reason why bland corporate malls are now a bigger part of Japan&#39;s shopping experience than they were two or three decades ago. But as <em>Emergent Tokyo</em> notes, there still are quite a few young Japanese people who want to start <em>new</em> small retail businesses, so hopefully this will be enough to sustain the kind of Japanese urbanism that the rest of the world has come to know and love. </p><div><hr></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?"><span>现在订阅</span></a></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/secrets-of-japanese-urbanism-part?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"> <a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/secrets-of-japanese-urbanism-part?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share"><span>分享</span></a></p><p></p>;
